; diverge_arg_walked — P-I reachability must still WALK the argument of a
; diverging control form, so a type error INSIDE it is reported (the arg-0
; walk). Here the thrown value is `(int_add "s" 1)` — `int_add` is declared
; `(int int)`, so passing a string is a CERTAIN mismatch. Even though `throw`
; never returns, its argument is evaluated, so the diagnostic must still fire
; (the reachability analysis annotates divergence WITHOUT cutting the walk).
(module stdlib.fixtures.diverge_arg_walked)
(bind boom (lambda () (throw (int_add "s" 1))))
(export boom)
